  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are caught massively short gamma with SPX at 6492.56, just 7 points below the monster -9.3B negative gamma wall at 6500, forcing them into momentum-amplifying hedging that's driving this breakout higher. With the market above the 6170 GEX flip in full breakout regime, dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward the 6490/6500 cluster and sell resistance into the 6605 positive gamma ceiling where they'll dump hedges. Watch for explosive moves as we're sandwiched between the largest negative gamma concentrations at 6500/6490 below and the positive gamma cap at 6605 above - any break of 6500 support triggers cascading dealer buying while a push through 6605 removes the gamma ceiling entirely.",
